title: For Sale:  1884 Springfield Trapdoor
postcontent: This is a Model 1884 US Springfield single shot Trapdoor 45/70 rifle.  It was manufactured in 1890; serial #435123. The rifle is in remarkable shape for being over 120 years old. The blueing has all turned to a gray patina and there is no color case hardening visable on the lock or side plates. There is no rust visable on this gun. The bore is bright and clean.  The rifle still retains the original Buffington, elevator rear sight which is worth around $225 by itself.  The rifle shoots the 405 grain bullet commonaly known as the 45/70 Government load available at any good sports store. This rifle can be used to hunt any game animal that walks on the North American continent. This rifle was sporterized at some point; barrel cut to 23"; Sears Robuck sold these in their catalog in 1900 for $2.50 each! It has two small pieces of wood missing next to the tang but nowhere else. Is a great gun to hang above the fireplace or lots of fun to shoot.Earlier percushion versions of this rifle saw use during the Civil War. This model also saw action with Custer during his last stand and neumerous other indian campaigns in the 1890s.  Also was used during the Spanish American war and the Phillipine American war.Own a true piece of American History!  Will consider shipping to your FFL.$450 Cash or Best OfferIllinois buyer must have valid FOID.

postcontent: I have for sale a new, in the box and unfired, Noveske Thunder Ranch rifle.  It comes with the Noveske sights(installed then taken off), two COA's signed by John Noveske along with Thunder Ranch's President and Vice President Clint and Heidi Smith, registration card and one normal capacity mag, everything new and perfect condition.  This rifle was built to be one of the lightest Noveske, then you know the quality and pride that went into the manufacturing and assembly of each of these rifles under John's supervision, top notch fit, finish and function.  I'm not saying anything negative about the rifles produced post John's death, I'd bet my life and my family's life on any of those too, but many people prefer rifles that were made prior to his death while he was overseeing everything.  One "Bigly" feature, in addition to everything else, is the barrel, it has a 14.5" CHF Skinny contour 1/7 twist barrel, made of Mil-Spec M249 Machine Gun barrel steel with heavy M249 chrome lining, appx. two times as thick as an M4 or M16, supposed to be good for 40,000 rounds, so perfect for any "SHTF", "WROL", "EOW" scenario, lol, I just call it the perfect "go to" title: For Sale:  CZ P-10 C 9mm FDE-SALE
postcontent: Product Description The Flat Dark Earth version of the P-10 C.Buy it online at www.copsgunshop.net.  All FFL rules and regs apply.  Buyer pays shipping or sales tax.  Sorry, no trades.  Many years in the making, we’re pleased to announce the latest addition to the CZ line of handguns — the P-10 C. Much more than just our take on the striker-fired pistol, the P-10 is decidedly CZ, from the way it feels to the way it shoots. First order of business, ergonomics. Anyone who’s picked up a CZ 75 for the first time gets it — it just has to feel right in the hand. With the CZ grip angle, the P-10 avoids that ‘brick-in-the-hand’ feeling that has plagued many in the striker-fired genre, allowing it to point naturally. A mild palm swell, deep beavertail and three interchangeable backstraps make the P-10 fit a wide variety of hands as if it were built for them. Because it was. Next up, trigger. So many striker-fired pistols do many things right, falling short when it comes time to pull the trigger. The P-10’s trigger is designed to minimize creep and stacking, and after initial break-in averages a clean 4.5-5 lb pull and rebounds with a short, positive reset — meaning single shots can be meticulously placed while follow-ups are effortless. Built to withstand the rigors of military use, its fiber-reinforced polymer frame and hardy nitride finish are made for the daily grind. A generous trigger guard allows use with gloved hands while being undercut to allow as high a grip as possible, and a set of metal tactical sights allow for one-handed manipulation of the slide on a belt. Like all CZ pistols, the P-10 is built with our legendary cold hammer forged barrel. The ‘C’ in the name indicates that it is compact in both frame and slide size, and magazines are of the same family as the hammer-fired P-07, meaning the P-10 C holds 15+1 in 9mm in a flush-fitting mag with extended bases allowing 17+1. Take-down of the P-10 will be familiar to most fans of striker-fired guns, and even more pleasing will be holster compatibility with some of the most common guns on the market. It may have taken a while to come to market, but we feel the wait has been worth it. With CZ reliability, engineered ergonomics and a bevy of features both familiar and new, the P-10 is the complete package.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Glock 17 .22TCM
postcontent: Up for sale or trade is a Glock 17 chambered in the  lightning fast .22TCM. If you haven’t heard of 22TCM it is a .223/5.56 case cut down to similar length as the 9mm and necked down to accept a 40 grain .22 caliber projectile that moves out of a 5” pistol barrel at 2200 feet per second. Hardly any recoil at all.These as things are an absolute blast to shoot! It is extremely loud and shoots flame 2-3 feet out of the barrel. They penetrate similar to a 5.7 and are very very accurate. You have to experience this round for yourself, it is a really fun pistol.
